  <dataqual>
    <attracc>
      <attraccr>Attribute data were extracted from the station listings in the Fall/Winter 1998 Amtrak National and Northeast Timetables, and reflect station characteristics as of October 25, 1998.</attraccr>
    </attracc>
    <logic>All point records are represented by a single coordinate pair and a unique feature identifier; the Amtrak Station Code stored in the FEATURID field). Attribute data can be matched to specific point records using this identifier.</logic>
    <complete>The database includes all Amtrak railroad and thruway bus stations listed in the 1998 Fall/Winter Amtrak Timetables. Also included are Amtrak railroad stations listed in earlier releases of this database that are now closed. Regional commuter railroad stations that are not also served by Amtrak are not included in this version; those stations are currently included in the Fixed-Guideway Transit Network database. The database does not include information on passenger boarding's; those data are considered to be proprietary by Amtrak.</complete>
    <posacc>
      <horizpa>
        <horizpar>Stations having valid street addresses were geocoded to 1995 TIGER/Line(TM) street and railroad centerline files. Positional accuracy for those points is consistent with the accuracy of 1995 TIGER/Line(TM) files, or within about 50 meters of their true position. Stations with ambiguous or incomplete street addresses (and stations located in Canada) were positioned using a combination of street name, nearest railroad centerline, and place name. Positional accuracy for these points may vary from 100 to 1000 meters of their true location.</horizpar>
      </horizpa>
    </posacc>
